body:
Quick fixes, renaming, code-highlighting, etc...are all constantly out of date and can take minutes to update.  I don't know if it's the AST parser, the dart parser, or what, but as I work on my very small Flutter project and I go to refactor, or edit, things are just, broken.

Example: In the following snippet, I had only just written line 14 `_repository.getServices()` which is a call to a method that returns a locally instantiated list of models, and pressed `ctrl+f6` to rename the method only to receive an error message that I 'could not rename the builder property`.  It wasn't until I navigated to the method itself and attempted to perform the refactoring directly that it finally 'worked' from the `FutureBuilder` instance.

```
import 'package:flutter/material.dart';
import 'package:snippy_client/repository/booking.dart';
import 'package:snippy_client/repository/booking/local.dart';
import 'package:snippy_client/repository/booking/models.dart';

class BookingBuilderPage extends StatelessWidget {
  BookingBuilderPage({Key? key}) : super(key: key);

  final BookingRepository _repository = BookingLocalRepository();

  @override
  Widget build(BuildContext context) {
    return FutureBuilder<List<BookingItem>>(
        future: _repository.getServices(),
        builder: (context, snapshot) {
          if (!snapshot.hasData) {
            return Container();
          } else {
            List<BookingItem> bookingItems = snapshot.data!;
            return ListView.builder(
                itemCount: bookingItems.length,
                itemBuilder: (context, index) {
                  return ListTile(title: Text(bookingItems[index].title));
                });
          }
        });
  }
}
```

In the code below, I had been prompted with a quick-fix to 'remove excess containers', but when I implemented the refactor using Ctrl+enter, the resulting code was mangled differently each time. Either the `return` keyword was dropped or the string in the `Text` class had the quotes placed incorrectly.

Before quick-fix:
```
import 'package:flutter/widgets.dart';

class FooWidget extends StatelessWidget {
  const FooWidget({Key? key}) : super(key: key);

  @override
  Widget build(BuildContext context) {
    return Container(child: Container(child: const Text("Unwrap me")));
  }
}
```

After quick-fix:
```
import 'package:flutter/widgets.dart';

class FooWidget extends StatelessWidget {
  const FooWidget({Key? key}) : super(key: key);

  @override
  Widget build(BuildContext context) {
    Container(child: const Text("Unwrap me"));
  }
}
```

